.TH FSEARCH "1" "2021-07-17"
.
.SH NAME
FSearch \- a graphical file search utility
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fsearch
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B fsearch config
.RI COMMAND " [" OPTIONS "]"
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B FSearch
allows you to search for files and folders by name. It uses an index to provide results almost instantly as you type.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Help Options"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\^\-help
Show help options
.TP
.BR \-\^\-help\-all
Show all help options
.SS "Application Options"
.TP
.BR \-\^\-minimized
Minimize the application window
.TP
.BR \-\^\-new-window
Open a new application window
.TP
.BR \-\^\-preferences
Show the application preferences
.TP
.BI \-s " PATTERN" "\fR,\fP \-\^\-search=" PATTERN
Set the search pattern
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\^\-update-database
Update the database
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\^\-version
Print version information and exit
.TP
.BI "\-\^\-display=" DISPLAY
X display to use
.
.SH COMMAND-LINE SEARCH
Use
.B \-\-cli
or set
.B FSEARCH_UI=CLI
to search the persisted FSearch index and print one path per line. Use
.B \-\-gui
to override the environment and launch the graphical interface. Run
.B fsearch \-\-cli \-\-help
for query syntax and examples.
.
.SH INDEX REFRESH POLICY
The graphical and command-line interfaces share one index and one persisted refresh policy. The default
.B auto
policy rebuilds when the index is missing or unreadable, its configured roots or exclusions changed, or an active root
was last scanned at least two hours ago.
.TP
.BR \-\-refresh ", " \-\-refresh\-index
Rescan before this command-line search. The two spellings are synonyms.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-reindex
Do not scan. A readable stale index remains searchable with a diagnostic on standard error; an unavailable index causes
the command to fail.
.TP
.BI \-\-reindex\-interval " SECONDS"
Override the automatic age threshold for this command-line search. A value of zero disables only age-based refreshes;
it does not suppress rebuilding a missing index or changed configuration.
.PP
Later conflicting command-line options win. The persistent keys
.B database.refresh-mode
(
.BR auto ,
.BR always ,
or
.BR never ) and
.B database.refresh-interval
(a non-negative number of seconds) are available through
.B fsearch config
and apply to both interfaces. Environment defaults
.B FSEARCH_REFRESH_MODE
and
.B FSEARCH_REFRESH_INTERVAL
override saved values for one process; command-line refresh options override both and never modify the configuration.
.
.SH CONFIGURATION COMMANDS
The
.B config
subcommand views and modifies the same configuration used by the graphical and command-line interfaces.
Close the graphical interface before modifying shared settings so its in-memory state cannot overwrite the command-line change.
Run
.B fsearch config \-\-help
for the complete command summary and examples, or append
.B \-\-help
to a command family for its specific syntax.
.TP
.BR path
Print the active configuration file path.
.TP
.BR show " [" SECTION "] [" \-\-json "]"
Show typed scalar settings, optionally restricted to a dotted section.
.TP
.BR get " " KEY " [" \-\-json "]"
Print one setting.
.TP
.BR set " " KEY " " VALUE
Set and persist one typed setting.
.TP
.BR unset " " KEY
Restore one setting to its default.
.TP
.BR reset " [" KEY | SECTION "] " \-\-yes
Restore a setting, section, or the complete configuration. Confirmation is mandatory. Add
.B \-\-rescan
when resetting roots, database, exclusions, or everything to rebuild the index immediately.
.TP
.BR doctor
Check whether the configuration is readable and agrees with the current index configuration.
.TP
.BR roots " " list | add | set | remove
Manage indexed root directories. Add and set accept
.BR \-\-active / \-\-inactive ,
.BR \-\-monitor / \-\-no\-monitor ,
.BR \-\-one\-file\-system / \-\-no\-one\-file\-system ,
.BR \-\-scan\-after\-launch / \-\-no\-scan\-after\-launch ,
and
.BI \-\-rescan\-every " SECONDS" .
.TP
.BR excludes " " list | add | remove | hidden
Manage exclusions with
.BI \-\-type " fixed|wildcard|regex" ,
.BI \-\-scope " full-path|basename" ,
and
.BI \-\-target " both|files|folders" .
.TP
.BR filters " " list | add | set | remove | reset
Manage named saved queries and macros with
.BR \-\-query ,
.BR \-\-macro ,
and paired
.BR \-\-case / \-\-no\-case ,
.BR \-\-path / \-\-no\-path ,
and
.BR \-\-regex / \-\-no\-regex
flags.
.PP
Root and exclusion changes mark the existing index stale. They are applied automatically by the next command-line search; pass
.B \-\-rescan
to an index-changing command to rebuild immediately. Collection list commands and scalar
.B show
and
.B get
support
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.
